-- ComplexNumber/trigonometric_series.math
--
-- The real power series of cosine and sine, harvested from the complex
-- exponential. Since cos x = Re(exp(ix)) and Re commutes with the
-- (convergent) partial sums, cos x is the limit of the real series
-- whose k-th term is Re of the k-th term of exp(ix); likewise sin x
-- with Im. The k-th term, evaluated through the i-power 4-cycle:
--   Re(term_{2m})   = (1/(2m)!)·(−x²)^m,   Re(term_{2m+1}) = 0,
--   Im(term_{2m})   = 0,                   Im(term_{2m+1}) = (1/(2m+1)!)·x·(−x²)^m,
-- i.e. cos x = Σ (−1)^m x^{2m}/(2m)! and sin x = Σ (−1)^m x^{2m+1}/(2m+1)!
-- once the vanishing terms are dropped (done in the bracketing layer).

module ComplexNumber.trigonometric_series

